Semprius Gets Funding for High-Efficiency Solar-Panel Factory

-- B y   A n d r e w   H e r n d o n
-- 
2011-06-29T21:32:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/semprius-gets-funding-for-high-efficiency-solar-panel-factory.html
Semprius Inc., a developer of
concentrating photovoltaic systems, received $20 million in
venture capital funding to build a pilot production plant.  Siemens AG (SIE)  led the funding round through its Siemens
Venture Capital unit, Durham, North Carolina-based Semprius said
today in a statement. Arch Venture Partners LP, Applied Ventures
LLC, Illinois Ventures LLC, Intersouth Partners, In-Q-Tel and
GVC Investment also participated.  The production plant will have an initial capacity of 5
megawatts and “will be expandable to 35 megawatts as needed,”
Semprius spokesman Dan Burke said today by e-mail. Siemens owns
a 16.1 percent stake in Semprius.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Herndon in  San Francisco  at 
 aherndon2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
